<item>
            <title>[SOLR-70] ping.jsp is very naive -- doesn&apos;t work with &quot;qt&quot; or any extra query args</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-70</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;while reviewing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-58&quot; title=&quot;Change Admin components to return XML like the rest of the system&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-58&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-58&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; i noticed that ping.jsp is &lt;b&gt;extremely&lt;/b&gt; naive about the types of requests it can use to sanity check the index, in particular:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it treats the first query param that starts with &quot;q&quot; as the query string (like for example &quot;qt&quot;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it ignores all other query params&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;...this makes it worthless to try and configure anything but the standard querest handler with no options as your ping URL.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
