                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12457040" author="hossman" created="Sat, 9 Dec 2006 02:06:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;improvement of the parsing, along with a comment in the example solrconfig.xml about exactly what kind of string should be in &amp;lt;pingQuery&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...fixed the issue where all params were ignored, and the first param that started with a &quot;q&quot; was used as a query (&quot;qt&quot; for example) but didn&apos;t try to change the format, or add any url-unescaping.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12458314" author="hossman" created="Thu, 14 Dec 2006 00:19:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commited variation of patch which worked against trunk (with newer XML based pages)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
